<paragraph blockId="2.[132,775,1785,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">
GALLS. — Galls (
<figureCitation box="[304,381,1785,1810]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[199,210,1571,1589]" captionTargetBox="[132,1454,217,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-285@8.[132,1455,217,1533]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Galls of: A, Barbotinia oraniensis (Barbotin, 1964); B, Aylax papaveris (Perris, 1840); C, A. minor Hartig, 1840; D, Iraella ionescui n. sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156648/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) irregularly rounded (
<quantity box="[601,682,1786,1810]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3 mm</quantity>
in diameter), light yellow, forming numerous individual chambers inside capsules of puppies (mainly in 
<taxonomicName box="[428,507,1838,1862]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Papaver" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhoeas">
<emphasis box="[428,507,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">P. rhoeas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[553,648,1838,1862]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Papaver" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dubium">
<emphasis box="[553,648,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">P. dubium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), attached to septa of the fruit capsule, originated by the transformation of the seeds. Poppy capsules are not deformed externally, so its presence is not visible from outside.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="507" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[130,775,1976,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">
COMMENTS. — Adults are very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perris" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[517,626,1976,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveris">
<emphasis box="[517,626,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">A. papaveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two species can only be recognized based on slight morphological differences,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[812,1456,1103,1259]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">
for this reason 
<bibRefCitation author="EADY R. D. &amp; QUINLAN J." box="[958,1196,1103,1127]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref7014" refString="EADY R. D. &amp; QUINLAN J. 1963. - Hymenoptera Cynipoidea Key to families and subfamilies and Cynipinae (including galls). Handbooks for the identification of British Insects 8 (1 a): 1 - 81." type="journal article" year="1963">Eady &amp; Quinlan (1963)</bibRefCitation>
questioned its differences. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[813,929,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[813,929,1129,1153]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">Aylax minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has notauli indistinct in the anterior ⅓, sometimes a very few impressions is present in anterior ⅓ (complete in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perris" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">A. papaveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), scutum only coriaceous (coriaceous usually with some weak rugosity in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perris" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[928,1045,1209,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveris">
<emphasis box="[928,1045,1209,1232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">A. papaveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and scapus + pedicellum usually lighter than flagellum (uniformly colored 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perris" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1152,1267,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveris">
<emphasis box="[1152,1267,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">A. papaveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[813,1455,1292,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507">
LIFE CYCLE. — Galls start to develop in spring, mature in May to June; adults emerge from capsules next spring. The life history of the species has been accurately studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="FOLLIOT R." box="[1223,1364,1344,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="507" pagination="407 - 564" refId="ref7057" refString="FOLLIOT R. 1964. - Contribution a l'etude de la biologie des Cynipides gallicoles (Hymenopteres, Cynipoidea). Annales des Sciences naturelles, Zoology 12, Ser. 6: 407 - 564." type="journal article" year="1964">Folliot (1964)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
